de.bioforscher.singa.mathematics.graphs.model

Class GenericGraph<ContentType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.bioforscher.singa.mathematics.graphs.model.AbstractMapGraph<GenericNode<ContentType>,GenericEdge<ContentType>,Vector2D,java.lang.Integer>
      • de.bioforscher.singa.mathematics.graphs.model.GenericGraph<ContentType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ContentType - The content type of the nodes.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Graph<GenericNode<ContentType>,GenericEdge<ContentType>,java.lang.Integer>

    public class GenericGraph<ContentType>
extends AbstractMapGraph<GenericNode<ContentType>,GenericEdge<ContentType>,Vector2D,java.lang.Integer>
    The generic graph class connects generic nodes with generic edges. Generic in this sense means, that any content can be associated to the nodes, connected by the edges.
